<HEADLINE>
<P>
AUSTIN STANTON; FOUNDER OF INNOVATIVE MILITARY EQUIPMENT FIRM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Austin Stanton, 91, founder of Varo Corp., which created night-vision 
telescopes and other high-tech equipment.A native of Iowa, Stanton earned a 
bachelor's degree in electrical engineering and a master's in physics from the 
State University of Iowa. He served as president of Geophysical Exploration Co. 
and Texas Geophysical Co., both in Dallas, and was an associate professor of 
electrical engineering at Southern Methodist University. In 1945, Stanton 
established Varo at his Garland, Tex., ranch with a contract to manufacture a 
"black box" for the military. Among the high-tech items he developed were 
electronic inverters and guided missile launch systems for military aircraft. 
On Sunday in Bonham, Tex. 
</P>
</TEXT>
