<HEADLINE>
<P>
WADE RICHARDS; GETTY MUSEUM EDUCATOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Wade Richards, 31, educator for the past five years at the J. Paul Getty 
Museum. His responsibilities included teaching in the galleries, organizing 
interactive exhibitions and administering the volunteer docent program.Last 
year, Richards was honored as the Pacific region educator of the year by the 
National Art Education Assn. An activist against AIDS, Richards was a founding 
member and served as co-chairman of the Alliance for Lesbian and Gay Concerns 
and helped focus the museum community's attention on AIDS. Among his articles 
in museum journals were "AIDS in the Workplace: What I Have Learned" and "The 
Interactive Gallery at the J. Paul Getty Museum." Richards had a bachelor's 
degree in religion and medieval studies from Duke University and a master's in 
archeology from UCLA. On Friday in Los Angeles of the complications of AIDS. 
</P>
</TEXT>
