<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: ANGELS HOPE TO SIGN RELIEVER LEE SMITH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB NIGHTENGALE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Angels have prepared a two-year contract offer for free-agent relief 
pitcher Lee Smith and hope to sign him within 10 days. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's very possible we could come to an agreement soon," Brian David, Smith's 
agent, said Thursday."We've been moving in a hurry." 
</P>
<P>
 The Angels, originally considered longshots in the bidding for Smith's 
services, are said to be willing to offer Smith a two-year guaranteed contract 
that would pay a base salary of about $2 million a year, plus incentives and 
award bonuses. 
</P>
<P>
 Smith earned a major league-leading 33 saves for the Baltimore Orioles last 
season and was on pace for his fourth consecutive 40-plus save season until the 
strike was called Aug. 12. Smith, 37, is baseball's all-time save leader and 
has posted at least 29 saves in 11 of the last 12 seasons. BOB NIGHTENGALE 
</P>
</TEXT>
