<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: CAMARILLO; SPRAYING OPPONENTS TO HOLD MEETING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A group opposed to the aerial spraying of malathion over eastern Camarillo 
will host a town hall meeting Monday that will feature a panel of doctors and 
scientists specializing in the health effects on people exposed to pesticides. 
</P>
<P>
 The meeting will be held in the Orchid Room of the United Food and Commercial 
Workers Hall, 816 Camarillo Springs Road, Camarillo, said Terri Gaishin, 
chairwoman of Group Against Spraying People, or GASP. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura County Supervisor Maggie Kildee will moderate the meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 Gaishin said GASP seeks to present the public with alternative views from 
medical doctors and scientists on the health effects of the spraying, which has 
been ordered by state agricultural officials to combat the Medfly infestation, 
discovered Sept. 29 in an east Camarillo orange grove. 
</P>
<P>
 Six panelists have been scheduled to appear for the 7 p.m. program, Gaishin 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information on the event or GASP, call 491-2495. J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
