</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KAY SAILLANT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Blue Cross of California is offering free health screenings today and Saturday 
for anyone who makes an appointment, a spokeswoman for the medical insurer 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The screenings -- which include tests for hypertension, cholesterol levels and 
skin cancer -- will be held from 8 a.m to 4 p.m. both days in the conference 
center at St. John's Regional Medical Center in Oxnard. 
</P>
<P>
 Interested residents must make an appointment before showing up at the center, 
said Stacey Doss, a spokeswoman for Blue Cross. The number to call is (800) 
274-9355. 
</P>
<P>
 Participants must also have a personal physician to whom test results can be 
sent, Doss said. 
</P>
<P>
 Each examination takes about 20 minutes, she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Blue Cross is offering the free service to Ventura County residents to gain 
exposure for its health insurance plans, Doss said. 
</P>
<P>
 More screenings may be offered later this year, she said. KAY SAILLANT 
