<HEADLINE>
<P>
RULES TO LIVE BY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBIN GREENE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Looking to teach your child some manners? Here are a few important ones 
recommended by Sally Fleer, who, from 1983 to 1989, taught a "White Gloves & 
Party Manners" class for Bullock's department stores: 
</P>
<P>
 * Always be prompt. * Stand when an adult comes into a room. * Introduce an 
older person first, make sure you make eye contact, and shake hands. * Always 
come to the dinner table with brushed hair and a clean face and hands. * Chew 
with your mouth closed. * Don't make an issue out of food you don't like. * 
Always RSVP an invitation. * Always write thank-you notes. * If you receive a 
gift by mail, write a thank-you note immediately.ROBIN GREENE 
</P>
</TEXT>
