<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; STANFORD'S DIEHL WINS 500-YARD FREESTYLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Eric Diehl, former Mission Viejo High star who now swims for Stanford, won the 
500-yard freestyle in 4 minutes 30.63 seconds, beating teammate Joe Hudepohl by 
more than a second Thursday at the UC Irvine Speedo Cup at Belmont Plaza Pool 
in Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 Stanford's men also won the 200 free relay (1:22.54) and the 400 medley relay 
(3:17.22). 
</P>
<P>
 In the 50 free, world record-holder Tom Jager was beaten by University of the 
Pacific's Brad Schumacher, who won in 20.31. Bjorn Zikarsky, who swims with the 
Irvine Novaquatics, placed sixth in 21.07. 
</P>
<P>
 In women's competition, the UCLA women won the 200 free relay and the 400 
medley relay. Competition continues today, and the meet concludes Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference women's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton 96, Loyola Marymount 74 -- Koko Lahanas scored 32 points 
and had 18 rebounds, and Shayla Bradshaw had 30 points and nine assists as 
Fullerton (1-1) won its first game. Loyola Marymount is 0-2. 
</P>
