<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOLLYWOOD PARK; RECORD PICK-SIX PAYOUT POSSIBLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hollywood Park's pick-six payout is expected to go well over $500,000 today as 
the exotic bet enters its third day without a winner. 
</P>
<P>
 No one has won the bet, in which you are required to pick the winner of six 
consecutive races, for two performances causing a carryover of $257,013. The 
usually large crowd tonight is causing race officials to estimate that a single 
ticket could return as much as $650,000. The record for a single pick-six 
ticket at Hollywood Park is $619,799, set in 1992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
