<P>
 Single-Family Home Sales Rise in State: Sales of detached homes were up for 
the third straight month, a sign that the battered market is recovering despite 
rising interest rates, the California Assn. of Realtors said. On a seasonally 
adjusted basis, the number of single-family detached homes that closed escrow 
during October was up 1.3% over September and 1% above October, 1993, the 
association said. At the same time, the median price of such homes was 
$180,100, down 0.7% from September and 2.4% below prices in October, 1993. 
