BRIEFLY: COMPANY TOWN ANNEX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 FCC May Increase TV Station Ownership Limit: The agency is finalizing a 
proposal to raise the maximum number of stations a single company can own, 
industry officials said.Under current rules, established to encourage diversity 
among TV owners and in programming, owners are limited to either 12 stations or 
a number that collectively serves no more than 25% of the U.S. population. Now, 
in recognition of industry competition, the Federal Communications Commission 
is floating a plan to raise the limit to 18 stations. It also has told industry 
officials that it will propose relaxing the population limit to 30% or 35%. 
</P>
