<P>
 Chemical Bank to Cut Jobs: In a sweeping austerity move, the New York-based 
company said it will eliminate 3,700 positions, sell most of its New Jersey 
operations and put nearly $1 billion in bad property loans on the 
block.Chemical Banking Corp. has been struggling to reduce expenses since it 
merged with Manufacturers Hanover Corp. in 1992. The actions will cost the 
nation's fourth-largest banking company about $410 million before taxes in the 
fourth quarter ending Dec. 30. Analysts estimated that the charge will reduce 
fourth-quarter earnings by 50 cents per share. 
