<TEXT>
<P>
 Purchasing Managers Report Increase: Manufacturing soared in November for the 
15th straight month and at the fastest pace in nearly 11 years, the National 
Assn. of Purchasing Management said.The group's purchasing managers index rose 
to 61.2% in November from 59.7% in October. Any figure over 50% points to 
manufacturing growth. The index was at its highest since February, 1984, when 
it was at 61.3%. In another report, the Commerce Department said Americans' 
incomes surged 1.4% in October, the biggest jump in eight months and the ninth 
straight gain. In yet another report, the Labor Department said the number of 
Americans filing the first time for state unemployment benefits dropped last 
week to the lowest level in two months. 
</P>
