some multiprocessor computers and has been corrected, Intel Corp. said. The 
disclosure of the additional flaw comes as the world's largest independent chip 
maker struggles to contain the furor about a flaw in the Pentium that wasn't 
disclosed by the company until a debate sprang up on the Internet. 
