<P>
 Help in Becoming Well-Heeled: Rose-Lee, a Beverly Hills-based footwear 
company, has designed shoes with interchangeable heels that allow women to 
change a heel's height from one inch to 3 1/2 inches.The shoes were designed by 
an orthopedic surgeon and a nurse practitioner who say they've seen an endless 
stream of patients complaining of back, knee and ankle pain that can be 
attributed to high-heeled shoes. The shoes come with two sets of heels, which 
can be unscrewed with a special key or a coin. The shoes will retail for about 
$90. 
