<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANGRY NOTE FROM BEETHOVEN AUCTIONED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An angry letter written by Beethoven, complaining about not being paid for a 
day's work, was sold for $25,160 at Sotheby's. 
</P>
<P>
 The auctioneers said the German composer, in an undated letter to a friend, 
wrote that he had proof of his presence in the Imperial Court theater in Vienna 
that day and said he had consulted his lawyers on the matter. 
</P>
<P>
 In one passage Beethoven says he wishes he were a bear so that he could knock 
down all the "asses" around him. He describes the directors of the theater as 
"vandals." 
</P>
</TEXT>
