<HEADLINE>
<P>
EX-NICARAGUA PRESIDENT SUFFERS HEART ATTACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Former President Daniel Ortega is hospitalized in Cuba after medical tests 
showed he suffered a minor heart attack three months ago, his Sandinista Party 
said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Ortega was in satisfactory condition at a specialized hospital in Havana, the 
Cuban capital, the party said. 
</P>
<P>
 Ortega, 49, president from 1985 to 1990, is secretary general of the 
Sandinista National Liberation Front and a leading contender for the party's 
presidential nomination in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
