<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: FOUNTAIN VALLEY; POLICE TO CONDUCT JOINT SOBRIETY 
CHECKPOINT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Fountain Valley and Westminster police departments will conduct a sobriety 
checkpoint between 10 tonight and 2:30 a.m. Saturday.The checkpoint will be 
near the border between the cities on Brookhurst Street near Edinger Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 The Fountain Valley Police Department has been conducting sobriety checkpoints 
since 1992. Police said the idea is to identify drivers who are intoxicated as 
well as to educate the public about the seriousness of driving while under the 
influence of alcohol or drugs. 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley Police Sgt. Kevin McKeown said that with the holiday season 
nearing, "if you do drink, find a designated nondrinking driver before you 
begin your celebrations." 
</P>
</TEXT>
