<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; CHOIRS TO JOIN LIGHTING CEREMONY 
TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Choral groups from local schools will sing tonight at Mission San Juan 
Capistrano as part of the city's tree-lighting festivities, which begin at 6 
p.m. at Del Obispo Street and Ortega Highway. 
</P>
<P>
 Choirs from elementary schools and high schools will perform from 6:45 to 7:15 
p.m. in the mission's center courtyard following the tree-lighting ceremony and 
flashlight procession. 
</P>
<P>
 A Las Posadas procession will leave from the mission at 7:30 p.m. and travel 
to the Los Rios Historic District, where a live Nativity pageant is planned. 
</P>
<P>
 Las Posadas is a Mexican celebration that enacts the search for lodging by 
Mary and Joseph. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is free to the public. Those who attend are encouraged to wear warm 
clothes and bring a flashlight. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 661-7117. JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
