<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; GROUP PICKS LOS AMIGOS CHIEF AS MAN OF YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Amin David, chairman of Los Amigos of Orange County, will be named Man of the 
Year this month because of his activism as a Latino advocate. 
</P>
<P>
 The Anaheim chapter of the League of United Latin American Citizens will honor 
David at an awards banquet Dec. 9 at the Grand Hotel, 7 Freedman Way in 
Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
 David is a longtime member of LULAC and numerous other Latino organizations, 
in which he helps promote awareness of Latino issues. He also serves as 
chairman of the Orange County Housing Corp., which provides resources for 
low-income families to buy homes. In addition, David serves on the Disneyland 
Community Service Award Committee, in which he helps select community activists 
to honor. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm just amazed at the number of people who come to Amin for everything and 
anything they need, whether it's help on a fund-raiser or help with problems 
with police. People are there for Amin to help and he reaches out and helps 
them," said Rose Jurado, president of the LULAC chapter. "Someone like that, 
you have to show some kind of appreciation for." 
</P>
<P>
 David said he was glad the banquet in his honor would be used to raise money 
for scholarships. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm very ill-at-ease to receive this award because it's with a tremendous 
degree of fulfillment that one does what one thinks has to be done," he said 
about his work. 
</P>
<P>
 The LULAC chapter has given the honor the past four years to men for their 
dedication to the Latino community. Other LULAC chapters in the county also 
honor people for their work. Santa Ana's chapter, for example, names a Woman of 
the Year and the Irvine chapter names an Educator of the Year. 
</P>
<P>
 The public is invited to the banquet, which will begin at 6:30 p.m. Tickets 
are $30 per person. To reserve seats, call Jurado at (714) 630-1678.MIMI KO 
</P>
</TEXT>
