<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The unincorporated community of North Tustin still retains a pastoral, sedate 
atmosphere that harkens back to the area's quiet history of citrus farming. 
</P>
<P>
 Bordered by the cities of Tustin and Orange, North Tustin is characterized by 
winding, tree-lined streets and green rolling hills. 
</P>
<P>
 A move to incorporate was launched by residents in 1991, but their bid was 
denied in early 1992 by the Local Agency Formation Commission. LAFCO said the 
bedroom community of 25,000 people didn't have the sales tax base to support 
cityhood. 
</P>
<P>
 In the past, some Tustin officials considered annexing North Tustin. But the 
current City Council has stayed away from the touchy issue. Today 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach will celebrate the season with special holiday activities at City 
Hall and throughout the downtown area. 
</P>
<P>
 Mr. and Mrs. Santa Claus are scheduled to arrive at 6 p.m. at City Hall in a 
fire truck parade starting from Laguna Beach High School. This will be followed 
by a tree lighting ceremony and musical performances. 
</P>
<P>
 Caroling and entertainment will continue until 9 p.m. along Forest Avenue, 
Ocean Avenue, Broadway, Beach Street and Coast Highway. 
</P>
</TEXT>
