COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: DANA POINT; SHELTER TO SPONSOR PET ADOPTION PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Animal Rescue Foundation of Dana Point is sponsoring a pet adoption 
program Saturday.Dogs, cats, puppies and kittens will be available from 9 a.m. 
to 1 p.m. at Lantern Bay Village, 24871 Del Prado Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Sheriff's deputies will present a demonstration of a canine patrol, and owners 
may obtain special microscopic identification chips for pets at a discount. 
</P>
<P>
 For dog owners whose pet licenses have expired, the event will offer a chance 
to renew them without being penalized. 
</P>
<P>
 The Animal Rescue Foundation is a nonprofit group dedicated to the welfare of 
stray and lost animals. For more information, call (714) 493-5251. 
</P>
