<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: IRVINE; NEWPORT MAN DIES AFTER CYCLE CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK I. PINSKY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 25-year-old Newport Beach resident was fatally injured Thursday when his 
motorcycle crashed into a stalled car on MacArthur Boulevard at Newport Coast 
Drive, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim's name was not immediately released. 
</P>
<P>
 Police Sgt. Scott Cade said the stalled car was in a traffic lane. Before 
officers arrived, three minor, rear-end collisions occurred as cars tried to 
avoid the vehicle. 
</P>
<P>
 As the drivers were exchanging information on the shoulder of MacArthur at 
1:15 p.m., the motorcycle struck the rear of the stalled car, which was still 
in the traffic lane, Cade said. 
</P>
<P>
 The motorcyclist died at Western Medical Center-Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said he had been wearing a helmet, but it apparently had not been 
strapped. It was found some distance from him. MARK I. PINSKY 
</P>
</TEXT>
