<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: WILLOWBROOK; BOY, 3, 
WOUNDS HIS MOTHER WITH FATHER'S ASSAULT RIFLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 3-year-old Willowbrook boy grabbed the assault rifle in the back seat of his 
father's car Thursday and fired the gun, seriously wounding his mother.  
</P>
<P>
 Elizar Arzate "has a toy assault rifle he plays with that is very similar to 
his father's real one," said Angie McLaughlin, a Sheriff's Department 
spokeswoman. 
</P>
<P>
 The shooting occurred about 10:40 a.m. in the 2100 block of East Shauer 
Street, she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Elizar Reyes, 29, had loaded his gun and put it in the back seat of his car. 
He put his son and daughter in the back of the car and was talking with his 
wife when the boy fired the weapon. The bullet went through the car door and 
hit Elvira Arzate, 30, in the arm. She was in serious condition at Martin 
Luther King Jr./Drew Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Reyes, booked on suspicion of storing a weapon accessible to children, was 
held on $15,000 bail. 
</P>
