<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: HOLLYWOOD; PROSTITUTE 
GETS 30 DAYS IN JAIL FOR DEATH THREAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A convicted prostitute was sentenced to 30 days in jail after pleading no 
contest to charges that she threatened to kill a woman who objected to her 
attire, City Atty. Jim Hahn said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 On Halloween night, Marcia Latrice Wilson, 19, of Van Nuys was standing at 
Sunset Boulevard and Stanley Avenue wearing an outfit consisting of a black 
bathing suit, a string bikini thong and see-through net panties.  
</P>
<P>
 A 29-year-old woman who lives nearby approached Wilson and expressed an 
objection to her outfit because children were out trick-or-treating. 
</P>
<P>
 Wilson threatened to stab the woman to death, according to Hahn. Two 
plainclothes officers saw the confrontation, Hahn said. 
</P>
<P>
 The city attorney's office charged Wilson with making a terrorist threat.  
</P>
<P>
 She pleaded no contest to the charge Tuesday before Hollywood Municipal Judge 
Anita Dymant, who imposed the 30-day jail sentence. Wilson also was placed on 
summary probation and ordered to stay away from the victim. 
</P>
</TEXT>
