<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: PACOIMA; FOOD 4 LESS TO MOVE INTO SHOPPING CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIM MAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Viva Market in Pacoima Plaza is, well, muerto.  
</P>
<P>
 But shoppers need not mourn the dead market: Food 4 Less will soon replace the 
closed Viva store at the same location. 
</P>
<P>
 Pacoima Plaza, one of only a handful of strip malls in the community, is 
getting a $1-million make-over care of the Piken Co., a Studio City-based 
developer that created the mall 10 years ago using federal Urban Development 
Action grant funds. 
</P>
<P>
 A major part of the upgrade includes conversion of the former Viva Market to a 
Food 4 Less supermarket, where shoppers will be asked to bag their own 
groceries. Other planned improvements at the 132,000-square-foot center at 
Glenoaks and Van Nuys boulevards include repaving and striping the parking lot, 
painting storefronts and additional landscaping. 
</P>
<P>
 Work on the project began recently, said Herbert Piken, president of the Piken 
Co. "When it's done, we plan to have it looking like a new shopping center." 
</P>
<P>
 Other tenants of Pacoima Plaza include Thrifty Drug, Burger King, Little 
Caesar and Trak Auto. 
</P>
<P>
 Conversion of the existing Viva Market to Food 4 Less is part of a regional 
expansion of the Food 4 Less chain, Piken said. TIM MAY 
</P>
</TEXT>
