<HEADLINE>
<P>
MISSING BOY'S BODY FOUND IN HOME OF BABY-SITTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Detectives investigating the disappearance of a 2-year-old Rialto boy found 
the toddler's body Thursday stuffed inside an ottoman at his baby-sitter's 
house, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The body of Marcus Anthony Jackson, who had been missing since Monday morning, 
was discovered a day after investigators said they believed the child had been 
murdered. 
</P>
<P>
 The baby-sitter, Betty Ann Mills, 28, was booked Wednesday for investigation 
of murder, and her roommate, Kimberly Gay Cole, 35, was booked as a possible 
accessory. The women already had been arrested for investigation of felony 
child endangerment in the child's disappearance. 
</P>
<P>
 Rialto police said earlier this week that Mills had admitted hitting the boy. 
Forensic investigators said they found blood and other evidence at Mills' home, 
leading them to suspect foul play. 
</P>
<P>
 But it was not until detectives searched Mills' home a second time that the 
boy's body was found. Police said the killers apparently stuffed the body into 
a tear in the underside of an ottoman and resealed the opening with duct tape. 
</P>
<P>
 The child's mother, Marcella Jackson, said she had left her son with Mills and 
Cole while she moved to a new apartment. The women had two other children 
besides Marcus in their care at the time. 
</P>
