<P>
DRUNK DRIVER KILLED AFTER LOSING CONTROL OF CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 27-year-old woman was killed Thursday afternoon when she lost control of her 
car on a winding road while driving under the influence of alcohol, the 
California Highway Patrol reported. 
</P>
<P>
 The woman sped into a curve on Bouquet Canyon Road, south of Vasquez Canyon 
near Santa Clarita at 2:30 p.m., and the car flipped eight times, hurling her 
90 feet from the auto, said Officer Richard Perez. 
</P>
<P>
 Perez said the woman, who was not identified pending notification of her 
relatives, was not wearing a seat belt. She died a short time later at Henry 
Mayo Hospital, he said. JEANNETTE REGALADO 
