<P>
BICYCLIST DIES IN DRIVE-BY ATTACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A bicyclist was shot from a passing car Thursday, then collapsed as he tried 
to flee his attacker on foot, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man, who was not identified, died at a local hospital an hour later, Los 
Angeles Police Detective Mike Coffey said. 
</P>
<P>
 The shooting occurred at 4:30 p.m. in the 10600 block of Crockett Street near 
Wheatland Avenue in Sun Valley, Coffey said. 
</P>
<P>
 The bicyclist, believed to be in his early 30s, was riding west on Crockett 
when a white car drove by and a gunman fired several shots, striking him in the 
chest and neck, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 "He ran half a block and then collapsed in front of a house," Coffey said. 
"Neighbors called 911 and brought out towels for his bleeding." 
</P>
<P>
 Police had no suspects but believe that a pistol was used, he said. JEANNETTE 
REGALADO 
