<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLDWELL BANKER TO HIRE 47 FOR O.C. CORPORATE HEADQUARTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS WOODYARD, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In a further sign that Orange County's economy is improving, Coldwell Banker 
said Thursday that it is planning to hire 47 full-time workers at its corporate 
headquarters. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're going to need a whole new slew of people," company spokesman Hugh Siler 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 In particular, the company is looking for computer programmers, database 
administrators, analysts and others. The company plans to buy newspaper 
advertisements and hold a job fair in January. 
</P>
<P>
 The company said it expects to hire the new employees by February. They would 
bring the Mission Viejo-based company's corporate employment to 501. 
</P>
<P>
 "During the next six weeks, we will be adding employees at a rate of nearly 
one per day," said Chandler Barton, president of Coldwell Banker Corp. 
</P>
<P>
 Most of the new employees will work in an international relocation services 
unit that was formed in conjunction with Integrated Systems Solutions Corp., an 
IBM subsidiary. Coldwell's other two major divisions manage its 300 
corporate-owned real estate offices and about 2,000 affiliates in the United 
States, Canada and Puerto Rico. 
</P>
<P>
 Besides the usual benefits, Coldwell is touting its on-staff physical 
therapist, fitness center, self-defense and aerobics classes, and health 
screening and testing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
