<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL '94-95': SUNSET LEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 ESPERANZA 03,17,09,08 1993-94 RECORDS OVERALL LEAGUE 18-9 7-3 02,11,18 COACH 
RECORD AT SCHOOL Mark Hill 100-61 04,20,05,06,05 RETURNING STARTERS YR. HGT. P 
Josh Greer Jr. 6-7 F/C Billy Omer Sr. 6-0 G 04,15,05,06,04 TOP RETURNERS YR. 
HGT. P Bryan Butler Jr. 6-4 F Almar Lim Sr. 5-10 G 04,15,05,06,05 TOP NEWCOMERS 
YR. HGT. P Jason Dillard So. 6-0 G Andy Gaulden Fr. 6-4 G/F Bryan Moore So. 6-5 
F/C Matt Munson So. 6-0 G Lonnie Tape Jr. 6-5 F/C OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 The Aztecs would like to challenge for the their third league championship in 
four seasons, but they will be without sharpshooting guard Mike Thimgan. "He 
helped us win two league titles and finish second one year," Hill said. "He's 
tough to replace. But we do have a dominating player." Hill said Greer will be 
among the county's best. The 6-7, 230-pound junior is a force in the post, and 
Hill said his perimeter game has also improved. Omer is back to start at the 
point, and his play will be also be key to Esperanza's success. Lim provides 
good shooting from three-point range, but more importantly he is the team's 
best defensive player. "This team has great chemistry," Hill said. "The kids 
all get along with each other. We also have depth. A number of guys will push 
for starting spots." Tape and Butler are among those players, and four 
underclassmen will also push to play more, including Gaulden, a 6-4 freshman. 
Gaulden's brother, Sean, is a 6-7 sophomore who could also make an impact. 
SCHEDULE 
</P>
<P>
 December 2-3 at Brea-Olinda tournament; 5-10 at In-N-Out Burger/Converse 
Classic; 13 at Santa Margarita; 15 vs. Capistrano Valley; 21 vs. Servite; 27-30 
at Orange Holiday Classic. 
</P>
<P>
 January 4 at La Mirada; 6 at Edison; 11 at Los Alamitos; 13 vs. Huntington 
Beach; 18 at Marina; 20 vs. Fountain Valley; 25 vs. Los Alamitos; 27 vs. 
Edison. 
</P>
<P>
 February 3 at Huntington Beach; 8 vs. Esperanza; 10 at Fountain Valley. 
</P>
